{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRTESTCD | Skin Response Test or Exam Short Name | Char | (SRTESTCD) | Topic | Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in SRTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in SRTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). SRTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRTEST | Skin Response Test or Examination Name | Char | (SRTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in SRTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Example: \"Wheal Diameter\". | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SROBJ | Object of the Observation | Char | | Record Qualifier | Used to describe the object or focal point of the findings observation that is represented by –TEST. Examples: the dose of the immunogenic material or the allergen associated with the response (e.g., \"Johnson Grass IgE 0.15 BAU mL\"). | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRCAT | Category for Test | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of topic-variable values across subjects. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSCAT | Subcategory for Test | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of SRCAT values. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRORRES | Results or Findings in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Results of measurement or finding as originally received or collected. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for SRORRES. Example: \"mm\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings copied or derived from SRORRES, in a standard format or in standard units. SRSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in SRSTRESN. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSTRESN | Numeric Results/Findings in Std. Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from SRSTRESC. SRSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized units used for SRSTRESC and SRSTRESN. Example: \"mm\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate exam not done. Should be null if a result exists in SRORRES. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRREASND | Reason Not Done | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Used in conjunction with SRSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRNAM | Vendor Name | Char | | Record Qualifier | Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provided the test results. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0376_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 376, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRSPEC | Specimen Type | Char | (SPECTYPE) | Record Qualifier | Defines the types of specimen used for a measurement. Example: \"SKIN\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
