{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRDY | Study Day of Visit/Collection/Exam | Num | | Timing | Actual study day of visit/collection/exam expressed in integer days relative to sponsor- defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRTPT | Planned Time Point Name | Char | | Timing | Text description of time when measurement should be taken. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See SRTPTNUM and SRTPTREF. Examples: \"START\", \"5 MIN POST\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num | | Timing | Numerical version of SRTPT to aid in sorting. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a fixed time point reference (SRTPTREF). Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 duration. Examples: \"-PT15M\" to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by EGTPTREF, \"PT8H\" to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by SRTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | Name of the fixed reference point referred to by SRELTM, SRTPTNUM, and SRTPT. Example: \"MANTOUX ADMINISTRATION\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| SRRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of the reference time point, SRTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Specification", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.4.5 Skin Response (SR)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SR – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "SR – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Skin Response (SR) domain is used to represent findings about an intervention, but it has its own domain code, SR, rather than the domain code FA.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0377_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 377, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "This domain is intended specifically for tests of the immune response to substances that are intended to provoke such a response (e.g., allergens used in allergy testing). SR is not intended for other injection-site reactions, including reactogencity events that may follow a vaccine administration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Because a subject is typically exposed to many test materials at the same time, SROBJ is needed to represent the test material for each response record. The method of assessment could be a skin-prick test, a skin-scratch test, or other method of introducing the challenge substance into the skin.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Any Identifier variables, Timing variables, or Findings general observation class qualifiers may be added to the SR domain, but the following qualifiers would not generally be used: --POS, --BODSYS, --ORNRLO, --ORNRHI, --STNRLO, --STNRHI, --STNRC, --NRIND, --RESCAT, --XFN, --LOINC, --SPCCND, --FAST, --TOX, --TOXGR, --SEV.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.4.5 Skin Response (SR)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SR – Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, the subject is dosed with increasing concentrations of Johnson grass IgE.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-4: Show responses associated with the administration of a histamine control.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 5-8: Show responses associated with the administration of Johnson grass IgE. These records describe the dose response to different concentrations of Johnson grass IgE antigen, as reflected in SROBJ.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "All rows show a specific location on the back (e.g., SITE1), represented in FOCID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
