{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, the study product dose, Dog Epi IgG, was administered at increasing concentrations. The size of the wheal is being measured (reaction to Dog Epi IgG ) to evaluate the efficacy of the Dog Epi IgG extract versus a negative control (NC) and a positive control (PC) in the testing of allergenic extracts. While SROBJ is populated with information about the substance administered, full details regarding the study product would be submitted in the Exposure (EX) dataset. The relationship between SR records and EX records would be represented using RELREC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0378_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 378, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-6: Show the response (description and reaction grade) to the study product at a series of different dose levels, the latter reflected in SROBJ. The descriptions of SRORRES values are correlated to a grade, and the grade values are stored in SRSTRESC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0379_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 379, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "SR – Examples", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7-12: Show the results of wheal diameter measurements in response to the study product at a series of different dose levels.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.5", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
